        <h2 class="left-heading destination-section-heading">Bridges &amp; Alcazar</h2>
        <p>On the northeastern side of Toledo is one of the historic entrances to the city, the stunning <strong>Alcantara Bridge</strong>, from which you can enjoy views looking up at the Alcazar palace and the city's walls.</p>
        <p>Just above the bridge is the massive 16th century <strong>Alcazar de Toledo</strong>, a former royal palace which is the most iconic sight in the city. The Alcazar was formerly the site of an ancient Roman palace, and today serves as a large Army Museum with historic weaponry and armor on display.</p>
        <h3>San Martin's Bridge &amp; Zipline</h3>
        <p>At the western edge of the walled old town is another incredible medieval bridge spanning the Taugus River, <strong>San Martin's Bridge</strong>. Both ends of the bridge are covered with fortified portals, and from the bridge you can enjoy great views over the river valley below.</p>
        <p>An even more exciting way to cross the Taugus River is to zipline over it at the extremely popular Fly Toledo, which travels alongside the bridge.</p>
    </section>


