        <h2 class="left-heading destination-section-heading">Museums</h2>
        <p>North of the Alcazar de Toledo is the walled city's main plaza, Zocodover, which is surrounded by impressive historic buildings.</p>
        <p>Adjacent to the Zocodover Plaza is the <strong>Museo de Santa Cruz</strong>, the city's main museum. This museum hosts exhibits in archaeology, decorative arts, and fine arts, including works by El Greco. The Santa Cruz Museum is housed within a former 16th century hospital which also hosts a lovely cloister.</p>
        <p>On the western side of Toledo is one of the city's most popular museums, the <strong>Museo del Greco</strong>, which recreates the home of the famous El Greco, who spent much of his life in Toledo creating art. The museum houses many of the artist's works, along with works by other 17th century Spanish artists.</p>
    </section>


