        <h2 class="left-heading destination-section-heading">Synagogues &amp; Monasteries</h2>
        <p>Nearby the Greco Museum are two beautiful medieval synagogues, including the 13th century <strong>Synagogue of El Transito</strong> which is known for its highly embellished stucco decor. Even older is the 12th century <strong>Synagogue of Santa Maria La Blanca</strong> is the oldest preserved synagogue in Europe. This structure is known for its ornate Moorish-style horseshoe arches which fill the interior.</p>
        <p>Also on the western side of the city near the synagogues is the <strong>Monasterio de San Juan de los Reyes</strong>, an intricate gothic monastery with a captivating exterior and a lovely cloister.</p>
    </section>




