        <h2 class="left-heading destination-section-heading">Northern Toledo Gates &amp; Medieval Mosque</h2>
        <p>On the northern side of the walled city is the <strong>Mezquita del Cristo de La Luz</strong>, a striking 1,000 year old mosque showcasing fine medieval Islamic architecture. From the Mezquita you can take in great views over Northern Toledo.
        <p>Just below the Mezquita is one of the city's most impressive medieval gates, the <strong>Puerta del Sol</strong>. To the north of this gate is Toledo's most famous gate, the incredible 10th century <strong>Puerta de Bisagra</strong>. Between the two city gates is a very scenic old street of the city you can walk along.</p>
    </section>


