    <section class="destination-section">
        <a class="anchor" id="hiking"></a>
        <h2 class="left-heading destination-section-heading">Hiking &amp; City Viewpoints</h2>
        <p>If you have extra time you might like to explore a bit below San Martin's Bridge as well, walking along the river.</p>
        <p>It's also possible to walk along the entire southern end of Toledo alongside the river between the two medieval bridges, passing along many rustic old buildings and ruins as well as waterfalls. This scenic riverside route between the San Martin's Bridge and Alcantara Bridge is approximately 1.8 miles (2.9 km) one-way.</p>
        <h3>Mirador del Valle City Overlook</h3>
        <p>A must-see attraction in Toledo is the <strong>Mirador del Valle</strong> viewpoint, which provides the iconic views overlooking Toledo from behind the river featured in many postcards. This viewpoint can be easily reached if you have a car, otherwise it's a 1.1 mile each way hike from the Alcantara Bridge.</p>
        <!-- Read More Read Less Tab -->
        <div class="hidden-content">
            <p>Instead of turning back around when you reach the Mirador del Valle viewpoint, you can continue to the San Martin's Bridge on the western side of Toledo for a total hiking length of about 2.9 miles if you like. Along this route you'll be able to enjoy multiple gorgeous perspectives overlooking Toledo's old town, tracing along the outer edge of the river bend.</p>
